    "On the other hand, the agreement between (4.14) and (4.15b) is less trivial.",
    "It amounts to an equivalence between field theory and asymptotic Hilbert spaces, known as asymptotic completeness.",
    "Concretely, this property ensures thatΨ |Ψ⟩⟨Ψ| = X |X⟩ in in ⟨X| = X |X⟩ out out ⟨X|.",
    "(4.16)As will become clear below, this is trivially manifest in perturbation theory.",
    "This is because the Feynman rules for computing (4.15b) in field theory involve the same cut propagators as those in X (defined in (3.5))."
